A tanker conveying fuel has exploded along the Lagos-Ibadan highway, DAILY POST reports. The tanker, it was gathered, fell and went up in flames around 6 am on Tuesday. A source at the scene of the incident, Adesanya Eniola, told DAILY POST that the incident occurred around Ogere Remo via Toll Gate, on the expressway. It was learnt that some vehicles were trapped in the incident, with traffic along that corridor affected. Details of the accident is still sketchy as of the time of filing this report. 